<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,513,646]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,513,538]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Comments.</emphasis>
In his treatise of carrot pests, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivnay" box="[653,820,513,538]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" refString="Rivnay, D. (1962) Field crop pests in the Near East. Vol. 10. Springer Science &amp; Business Media, Dordrecht, 450 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 017 - 1544 - 7" type="book" year="1962">Rivnay (1962)</bibRefCitation>
stated that “in 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1068,513,538]" name="Israel" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Israel</collectingCountry>
... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1848" box="[1111,1268,514,537]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Trioza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricornis">
<emphasis box="[1111,1268,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">T. nigricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodkinson" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Bactericera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trigonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Bactericera trigonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] is the common species, and not 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[630,747,549,574]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Trioza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis box="[630,747,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">T. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1848" box="[779,947,549,574]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Trioza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[779,947,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Trioza apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] as was formerly believed (
<bibRefCitation author="Rivnay" box="[1261,1413,549,574]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" refString="Rivnay, D. (1960) On the identity of the psyllid on carrots in Israel. Hassadeh, 40 (8), 957. [in Hebrew]" type="journal article" year="1960">Rivnay 1960</bibRefCitation>
).” It is not clear if Rivnay had actually seen specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foerster" authorityYear="1848" box="[772,889,585,610]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Trioza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[772,889,585,610]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">T. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1024,585,610]" name="Israel" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Israel</collectingCountry>
. We did not examine any material of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[348,410,621,646]" name="Israel" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Israel</collectingCountry>
and do not, therefore, include it in the list of Israeli 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1807" box="[995,1115,621,646]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Psylloidea">Psylloidea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
